About Me

Welcome to the Yanga Mdede tech Zone: Where Code & Hacking Drives Innovation!

Finally, we can talk about me, a blend of creativity and funny jokes (life's hard let's laugh...)

I fell in love with computing and electronics growing up. At age 7, I was fascinated with how my toys could talk, how light switches worked, why the toaster stopped working, and in no time I whipped out a screwdriver to examine what was under the boot of my toys. Even when I got to play with my toys like every other boy my age, I knew without a doubt I craved for much more. I like to believe I was born with an innate skill to do all these. I fell in love with solving problems and I relished every opportunity I got to fix something. I learnt quickly as I was curious and this lead me to experiment more and more. With time using a computer or being the family electrician was not a difficult feat. And now with God's grace here I am, a programmer at Capaciti (for BSG).

I did a Bsc in Computer Science, I have explored various fields in tech, including coding, web development, and hacking. Along the way, I developed a passion for learning new technologies and improving my skills. Through my work with HackerRank and self-directed projects I discovered the power of tech integration across different industries and became particularly fascinated with how technology can enhance everyday life.

A passionate and detail-oriented software developer with expertise in Ethical Hacing, Java, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, and googling. Experienced in building web applications. Skilled in resume building, script writing, and problem-solving, having completed a 90-day DSA challenge. entrepreneurial and leadership abilities. Eager to contribute technical and creative skills to innovative projects

And, to leave you with some motive from myside: Every Failed Interview Is a Lost Opportunity to Be at a Better Place

HackerRank is an online learning platform focused on providing high-quality education in programming, data structures, algorithms, and software development. Ethical Hacking Essentials (EHE) - Check Here!!
Jun 2023 - 13th Aug 2023 | EC-Council

The Ethical Hacking Essentials (EHE) course on EC-Council provides a foundational understanding of ethical hacking and cybersecurity practices. This course covers key topics such as network security, system vulnerabilities, penetration testing, and safeguarding against cyber threats. Designed for beginners, it emphasizes hands-on learning through practical scenarios and tools commonly used in ethical hacking. Completing this course equips learners with essential skills to identify, analyze, and mitigate security risks, fostering a proactive approach to maintaining secure systems and networks.

EC-Council is a leading online learning platform that partners with top universities and organizations worldwide to offer a wide range of courses, specializations, and degree programs. It provides learners with access to high-quality education in various fields, including technology, business, data science, arts, and personal development.
